Question: Explain to a younger friend how to apply for a college.
Answer:
Firstbof all, you need to take a SAT exam during your sophomore or junior year. Then, you have a select a few college you want to go. You can do it through looking on its website, asking people who have been to that college or even coming in for a campus tour. Once you know where you want to apply, you can start preparing for the materials for the college, such as personal statement, resume etc.